<section class="card"><h1>Integration command center</h1><p>This dashboard presents tenant onboarding, connector posture, event tracing, DLQ triage, contract catalog, and architecture guidance. If the API is offline, each route shows a controlled error state instead of crashing.</p></section>
<div class="grid"><section class="card"><h2>Business flow</h2><p>LMS and SIS events become governed CloudEvents-like messages, routed through Camel, persisted in MariaDB, and published to Kafka-compatible infrastructure.</p></section><section class="card"><h2>Security posture</h2><p>OIDC validation is enforced by default. Local dev auth is opt-in only through DEV_AUTH_ENABLED=true.</p></section><section class="card"><h2>Operational posture</h2><p>Every event carries tenant_id and correlation_id, with trace and DLQ lookup for support and audit workflows.</p></section></div>
